@afbjorklund I am little bit lost in discussion here (I started looking at in just now):
>For some reason, they lost the path support in the urls on the way - original PR did use it, but it doesn't work in what got merged...

what do you mean by that

```go
	callback := ssh.InsecureIgnoreHostKey()
	if secure {
		host := _url.Hostname()
		if port != "22" {
			host = fmt.Sprintf("[%s]:%s", host, port)
		}
		key := terminal.HostKey(host)
		if key != nil {
			callback = ssh.FixedHostKey(key)
		}
	}
```
Actually it looks like that if the key is not known then `ssh.InsecureIgnoreHostKey()` is used, which doesn't sound much secure.
Yeah I know it's not code from this PR.

